				<div class="panel-body">
					<ol style="text-align: justify;">
						<li>Suppose a group of 3 students wants to form a group, they should decide an admin among themselves. Only the admin of a particular group will be allowed to book a room on the day of the allotment. So choose someone with a good internet connection and someone who ll be free on the day of allotment, 14th to 16th tentatively.</li>
						<li>Admin with registration number "x"  clicks on the "My group" link on this page.</li>
						<li>Admin creates a group by giving it a name.</li>
						<li>Admin enters registration number "y" of his friend and clicks on "Invite Roommate". Remember that you can only send requests to students of your gender and year and category(JEE) .</li>
						<li>Admin enters registration number "z" of his other friend and clicks on "Invite Roommate". Admin will not be allowed invite roommates after his group has reached it's maximum capacity.</li>
						<li>The other roommates login, and click on "Received Requests". They do not need to create a group of their own.</li>
						<li>They can see a request from Sender with registration number "x" and they accept it.
						ðŸ˜Ž All three of them can see group details once requests are accepted.</li>
						<li>You can send request only to those of same course,year and admission type (JEE,DASA)as yours.</li>
						<li> You are allowed to form a group of size less than the maximum size as well</li>
						<li> In case of PG - Only students of same course can form group together i.e. Mtech with only Mtech,MCA with MCA , Msc with Msc , Msc.Tech with Msc.Tech ,MBA with MBA only.</li>
						<li>Happy Omaha</li>
